		<p>The dark shade character is a good fit when compared with the full block character because it makes the redacted text less prominent and make the surrounding text more readable.</p>
	</li>
	<li>Make the redacted text need to be in its own container. like: <code>&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</code></li>
	<li>Add the attribute <code>role="img"</code> to the redacted text container.</li>
	<li>Add the attribute <code>aria-label="Redacted text"</code> and modify the label accordingly to your context of use.</li>
	<li>Add CSS class <code>.redacted</code> for an inline redacted text</li>
	<li>If there no requirement to specify the number of redacted character, use the same amount of dark shade character for each redacted section and you will be able to reuse the same text label</li>
	<li>If you need to specify the number of redacted character, add the dark shade character inside the container to be the same as the number of redacted character. Also, adjust the text label accordingly.</li>
